"n.马笼头；v.抑制，控制 【英】 n.马笼头(a head harness)；v.抑制，控制(to curb or control) 【考】 反义词：without restraint(没有控制 的) 【记】 比较bride(新娘)，在 婚后的生活中，新娘 可能给新郎上笼头(Th e bride puts a bridle on the bridegroom.) 【例】 Bridle your tongue and be more careful about what you say. n. /v. (对欲望的)抑制, 控制 = curb = control; n 马笼头(安放在马头周围, 用来限制或引导的一种马具, 包括笼头、马勒和缰绳) 【例】Bridle your tongue 说话要谨慎. 【记】1)bride(n 新娘), 婚后新娘会控制新郎, 成为半边天. 2)读: 不愿动. 因为被抑制, 控制了. 3)来自ride骑, 前边有个b不: 不骑. 用马笼头来实现. 【反】without restraint(没有控制) 【记】bride 新娘，一结婚就等于新娘给新郎戴上笼头；音：被 ride 骑，被人骑就是被控制，上了马笼头 【相关】braid bridle (n.)  Old English bridel ""bridle, rein, curb, restraint,"" related to bregdan ""move quickly,"" from Proto-Germanic *bregdilaz (see braid (v.)). bridle (v.)  ""to control, dominate,"" c.1200, from Old English bridlian ""to fit with a bridle,"" from bridel (see bridle (n.)). Meaning ""to throw up the head"" (as a horse does when reined in) is from mid-15c. Related: Bridled; bridling."
